GeminvoiceSetupInstructionsTitle = Prerequisites: Google Cloud Platform Configuration
GeminvoiceSetupInstructions = To enable Geminvoice to read invoices from Google Drive and analyze them with Google Gemini AI, follow these steps:\n1. Create a project on the <a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/" target="_blank">Google Cloud Console</a>.\n2. Enable "<b>Google Drive API</b>" and "<b>Generative Language API</b>" in the API Library.\n3. Create an "API Key" in the Credentials section. Enter this key in the "Google Gemini API Key" field below.\n4. Create a "Service Account", generate a JSON key, and download it. Open the file and copy the raw JSON content into the "Google Service Account (JSON)" field below.\n5. Go to your "Invoice Scan" folder in Google Drive, click "Share", and add the Service Account email address (ending in @your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com) as an Editor.\n6. Copy the folder ID from the address bar (e.g., google.com/drive/folders/<i>1ABC2DEF3GHI</i>) into the "Google Drive Folder ID" field.
GeminvoiceGoogleSDKDesc = The module requires the Google APIs Client libraries (Google Drive, Generative Language). They must be installed in the module's <code>vendor/</code> folder via Composer.

