GeminvoiceDocIntroSummary = Welcome to the Geminvoice Help Center.
GeminvoiceDocWhatIsIt = What is Geminvoice?
GeminvoiceDocIntroDesc = Geminvoice is an AI-driven accounting intelligence module for Dolibarr. It automates supplier invoice entry and accounting code assignment (staging) from multiple sources: PDFs via Google Drive, manual uploads, Factur-X, or PDPConnectFR electronic invoices.
GeminvoiceDocWorkflowTitle = Standard Workflow
GeminvoiceDocWorkflowStep1 = Import documents (Google Drive, Upload, or Factur-X)
GeminvoiceDocWorkflowStep2 = Automatic analysis by OCR and Artificial Intelligence (Google Gemini)
GeminvoiceDocWorkflowStep3 = Human review to validate lines, third parties, and taxes
GeminvoiceDocWorkflowStep4 = Create the final Dolibarr invoice in one click

GeminvoiceDocPrerequisites = Prerequisites
GeminvoiceDocPrereq1 = A Google Cloud account with the Gemini API enabled
GeminvoiceDocPrereq2 = Google dependencies installed via Composer (<code>composer install</code> in the module folder) — only required for the Google Drive source
GeminvoiceDocPrereq3 = Module access rights configured for your users (read and write)

GeminvoiceDocSetupSummary = This section explains how to configure the module for the first time and verify that all connections are working.
GeminvoiceDocSetupStepByStep = Configuration steps
GeminvoiceDocSetupStep1 = Enter your Gemini API key — it is required for all sources (OCR and product recognition).
GeminvoiceDocSetupStep2 = To enable the Google Drive source: also add the Google Service Account JSON and the Drive folder ID to monitor. Share that folder with the service account email address.
GeminvoiceDocSetupStep3 = Check the connection indicators — all must be green before the first import.
GeminvoiceDocSetupStep4 = For automation: enable the Geminvoice scheduled task in Dolibarr's Scheduled Tasks module (recommended frequency: every hour).
GeminvoiceDocSetupWarning = Without a valid Gemini API key, OCR import and product recognition are entirely disabled. This is not an optional setting.

GeminvoiceDocIndicatorsTitle = Connection indicators
GeminvoiceDocIndicatorsDesc = On the configuration page, ensure that all indicators are green before using the module.
GeminvoiceDocIndicatorComposer = Google libraries (Composer) installed
GeminvoiceDocIndicatorGemini = Valid Gemini API key
GeminvoiceDocIndicatorDrive = Google Drive access working (if Drive source is configured)

GeminvoiceDocSourcesSummary = Geminvoice accepts three input modes. Each is suited to a different context — they can coexist.
GeminvoiceDocGdriveDesc = The module automatically monitors a Google Drive folder you define. Drop a PDF or image file into that folder — it will be imported on the next cycle (CRON or manual sync). The file is marked as processed after analysis to prevent re-import.
GeminvoiceDocGdriveNote = Requires the Google Service Account configured in the setup page.
GeminvoiceDocUploadDesc = From the dashboard, use the "PDF / Image Import" panel to drop one or more files directly from your computer. Gemini AI analysis starts immediately.
GeminvoiceDocFacturxDesc = For invoices in Factur-X format (European standard EN 16931) or ZUGFeRD: drop the PDF/A-3 or XML file in the dedicated panel. No OCR needed — data is read directly from the embedded structured XML, guaranteeing maximum accuracy.
GeminvoiceDocFacturxNote = Factur-X is the fastest and most reliable format. It is also the format that will be mandated by French e-invoicing regulations (expected 2026-2027).

GeminvoiceDocDashboardSummary = The dashboard is your queue. It lists all imported invoices pending validation, in error, or already processed.
GeminvoiceDocListTitle = Understanding the list
GeminvoiceDocListDesc = Each row represents a detected invoice. Columns show the source file, recognized vendor, invoice number and amounts extracted by OCR.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeDesc = Colored badge indicating the invoice origin: Google Drive (blue), manual upload (green), Factur-X (purple).
GeminvoiceDocDuplicateDesc = Orange alert if an identical invoice number already exists for this vendor in Dolibarr. Verify before validating.
GeminvoiceDocActionsTitle = Available actions
GeminvoiceDocActionReview = Review — opens the full review page to check each line.
GeminvoiceDocActionValidate = Validate without review — creates the Dolibarr invoice directly if you trust the OCR result.
GeminvoiceDocActionReject = Reject — permanently discards the invoice (no Dolibarr record created).
GeminvoiceDocActionRetry = Retry — re-runs AI analysis on a failed file.

GeminvoiceDocReviewSummary = The review page is the heart of the module. It lets you verify, correct and enrich extracted data before creating the Dolibarr invoice.
GeminvoiceDocReviewHeader = Invoice header
GeminvoiceDocReviewSocMatch = The module automatically looks up the vendor in Dolibarr by name (exact then fuzzy match). A badge shows the result: green for a reliable match, orange for an approximate match (click to confirm), red if no vendor was found (a new third party will be created).
GeminvoiceDocReviewCreditNote = If the document is a supplier credit note, check the "Supplier credit note" box. OCR detects it automatically in most cases — verify anyway. Geminvoice will then create a Dolibarr credit note (type 2) instead of a standard invoice.
GeminvoiceDocReviewCurrencyWarning = An orange banner appears if the currency detected by OCR differs from the currency set in Dolibarr. Verify amounts before validating.
GeminvoiceDocReviewTable = Lines table
GeminvoiceDocReviewTableDesc = Each OCR-extracted line is shown with its description, quantity, unit price excl. VAT, VAT rate, accounting code and associated Dolibarr product.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeLearned = 🧠 Memorized — this accounting code (or product) was learned during a previous validation for this exact line description.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeText = 🔍 Text match — match found by text similarity between the OCR description and the product catalog.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeAI = 🤖 Gemini AI — the code or product was suggested by Gemini artificial intelligence.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeVendor = 🏢 Vendor — default accounting code memorized for this vendor, used as a last resort.
GeminvoiceDocBadgeManual = ✏️ Manual — no automatic suggestion was found, free entry required.
GeminvoiceDocLineTools = Line tools
GeminvoiceDocLineSplit = ✂️ Split — splits one line into two. Useful when an OCR line combines two different natures.
GeminvoiceDocLineDuplicate = ⮟ Apply to all — propagates this line's accounting code to all other lines in one click.
GeminvoiceDocLineAdd = + Add a line — manually inserts an additional line not detected by OCR.
GeminvoiceDocLineMemorize = "Memorize" checkbox — check to have Geminvoice remember this accounting code for future invoices with the same description.
GeminvoiceDocLineParafiscal = "Parafiscal" checkbox — check for taxes such as TICPE, CVO, CRPV (0%% VAT, specific accounting treatment).
GeminvoiceDocLineInvert = ⚠️ Invert badge — appears on lines whose description contains "credit", "discount", "rebate" with a positive amount. Click to invert the sign.
GeminvoiceDocConsistency = Total consistency
GeminvoiceDocConsistencyDesc = The table footer calculates the line total HT and TTC in real time and compares it to the OCR header. A CONSISTENT / ERROR badge indicates whether amounts match. A consistency error does not block validation but should be explained.
GeminvoiceDocValidation = Final validation
GeminvoiceDocValidationStep1 = Check the consistency badge (CONSISTENT recommended).
GeminvoiceDocValidationStep2 = Select the vendor fallback accounting code if needed.
GeminvoiceDocValidationStep3 = Click "Validate and create Dolibarr invoice" — the invoice is created as a draft and the source PDF is archived in the Dolibarr DMS.

GeminvoiceDocMappingsSummary = The Mappings page lets you view and manage the rules Geminvoice has learned, and create new ones manually.
GeminvoiceDocMappingsTitle = Two types of rules
GeminvoiceDocMappingsLine = Line description rules — associate a label keyword with an accounting code, VAT rate and Dolibarr product.
GeminvoiceDocMappingsVendor = Vendor mappings — associate a vendor with a global accounting code used as a last resort on all its lines.
GeminvoiceDocMappingsAuto = These rules are created automatically at each validation when the "Memorize" checkbox is checked on the line.
GeminvoiceDocPriorityTitle = Full priority chain (6 levels)
GeminvoiceDocPriorityDesc = P1 🧠 Memorized rule → P2 🔍 Text match ≥ threshold → P3 🤖 Gemini AI (if enabled) → P4 🔍 Text match best effort → P5 📄 Raw OCR suggestion → P6 🏢 Vendor fallback accounting code

GeminvoiceDocErrorsSummary = This section describes the most common errors and how to resolve them.
GeminvoiceDocErrorsTypes = Error types
GeminvoiceDocErrorOCR = AI analysis error — Gemini OCR could not extract data (poor scan quality, protected document, unsupported format). Action: click "Retry" after improving the source file, or upload a more legible version.
GeminvoiceDocErrorDrive = Drive download error — the module could not access the file. Verify that the service account still has access to the shared Drive folder and that the authentication JSON is up to date in the configuration.
GeminvoiceDocErrorStaging = Staging error — database issue during record creation. Check Dolibarr logs for details.
GeminvoiceDocErrorResolution = For in-depth diagnosis: Admin → Tools → Logs (log files), or enable Dolibarr debug mode.
GeminvoiceDocErrorPurge = "Clear errors" button — removes all error entries from the list without affecting validated or pending invoices.
